intro: Cybele cunninghamii, commonly known as the Cunningham's cybele, is a rare flowering plant native to the mountainous regions of eastern Australia. It is characterized by its striking violet-blue flowers and is often found growing in rocky or sandy soils. The plant has a compact growth habit with small, lance-shaped leaves that are covered in fine hairs. It is typically found in open forests and shrublands, where it thrives in well-drained conditions. Due to its limited distribution and habitat specificity, it is considered a vulnerable species.
